\\\",\\n   131\\t        },\\n   132\\t        \\\"coupling_anchor_resolution\\\": {\\n   133\\t            \\\"outgoing_resolution\\\": \\\"skeleton_node\\\",\\n   134\\t            \\\"incoming_resolution\\\": \\\"skeleton_node\\\",\\n   135\\t            \\\"outgoing_anchor_type\\\": \\\"skeleton_node\\\",\\n   136\\t            \\\"incoming_anchor_type\\\": \\\"skeleton_node\\\",\\n   137\\t        },\\n   138\\t        \\\"serialization_requirements\\\": {\\n   139\\t            \\\"planner_record_fields\\\": [\\n   140\\t                \\\"root_id\\\",\\n   141\\t                \\\"morphology_class\\\",\\n   142\\t                \\\"source_project_role\\\",\\n   143\\t                \\\"promotion_rank\\\",\\n   144\\t            ],\\n   145\\t            \\\"shared_readout_requirement\\\": (\\n   146\\t                \\\"emit the same shared readout IDs on simulator_result_bundle.v1 timebase\\\"\\n   147\\t            ),\\n   148\\t            \\\"class_specific_extension_policy\\\": (\\n   149\\t                \\\"skeleton-resolved diagnostics may live under extensions while shared comparison artifacts remain unchanged\\\"\\n   150\\t            ),\\n   151\\t        },\\n   152\\t        \\\"approximation_notes\\\": [\\n   153\\t            \\\"Resolves branch-local and path-local variation while omitting explicit surface-sheet geometry and patch-level tangential spread.\\\",\\n   154\\t            \\\"May use skeleton-node anchors for coupling and readout, but promotion must preserve coupling sign, delay, and root-level observable semantics.\\\",\\n   155\\t        ],\\n   156\\t        \\\"class_specific_behaviors\\\": [\\n   157\\t            \\\"Can express branch-local timing or attenuation that a point neuron cannot, but not surface-sheet effects reserved for surface neurons.\\\",\\n   158\\t        ],\\n   159\\t    },\\n   160\\t    SURFACE_NEURON_CLASS: {\\n   161\\t        \\\"canonical_project_role\\\": ROLE_SURFACE_SIMULATED,\\n   162\\t        \\\"promotion_rank\\\": 2,\\n   163\\t        \\\"required_local_assets\\\": [\\n   164\\t            \\\"processed_surface_mesh\\\",\\n   165\\t            \\\"fine_surface_operator\\\",\\n   166\\t            \\\"coarse_patch_operator\\\",\\n   167\\t            \\\"surface_transfer_operators\\\",\\n   168\\t            \\\"surface_operator_metadata\\\",\\n   169\\t            \\\"root_local_synapse_registry\\\",\\n   170\\t            \\\"incoming_anchor_map\\\",\\n   171\\t            \\\"outgoing_anchor_map\\\",\\n   172\\t            \\\"root_coupling_index\\\",\\n   173\\t            \\\"selected_edge_coupling_bundles\\\",\\n   174\\t        ],\\n   175\\t        \\\"optional_local_assets\\\": [\\n   176\\t            \\\"raw_mesh\\\",\\n   177\\t            \\\"raw_swc_skeleton\\\",\\n   178\\t            \\\"geometry_descriptors\\\",\\n   179\\t            \\\"geometry_qa\\\",\\n   180\\t        ],\\n   181\\t        \\\"realized_state_space\\\": {\\n   182\\t            \\\"state_space_kind\\\": \\\"distributed_surface_field\\\",\\n   183\\t            \\\"state_axes\\\": \\\"per_surface_vertex_with_patch_projection\\\",\\n   184\\t            \\\"state_layout_semantics\\\": \\\"surface_activation_velocity_optional_recovery\\\",\\n   185\\t            \\\"local_geometry_resolution\\\": \\\"simplified_surface_mesh_with_coarse_patch_readout\\\",\\n   186\\t        },\\n   187\\t        \\\"readout_surface\\\": {\\n   188\\t            \\\"local_readout_surface\\\": \\\"coarse_patch_cloud\\\",\\n   189\\t            \\\"shared_readout_value_semantics\\\": DEFAULT_SHARED_READOUT_VALUE_SEMANTICS,\\n   190\\t            \\\"comparison_observable\\\": \\\"root_local_activation_summary\\\",\\n   191\\t        },\\n   192\\t        \\\"coupling_anchor_resolution\\\": {\\n   193\\t            \\\"outgoing_resolution\\\": \\\"coarse_patch\\\",\\n   194\\t            \\\"incoming_resolution\\\": \\\"coarse_patch\\\",\\n   195\\t            \\\"outgoing_anchor_type\\\": \\\"surface_patch\\\",\\n   196\\t            \\\"incoming_anchor_type\\\": \\\"surface_patch\\\",\\n   197\\t        },\\n   198\\t        \\\"serialization_requirements\\\": {\\n   199\\t            \\\"planner_record_fields\\\": [\\n   200\\t                \\\"root_id\\\",\\n   201\\t                \\\"morphology_class\\\",\\n   202\\t                \\\"source_project_role\\\",\\n   203\\t                \\\"promotion_rank\\\",\\n   204\\t            ],\\n   205\\t            \\\"shared_readout_requirement\\\": (\\n   206\\t                \\\"emit the same shared readout IDs on simulator_result_bundle.v1 timebase\\\"\\n   207\\t            ),\\n   208\\t            \\\"class_specific_extension_policy\\\": (\\n   209\\t                \\\"surface-resolved diagnostics may be written under extensions, but shared comparison payloads remain class-invariant\\\"\\n   210\\t            ),\\n   211\\t        },\\n   212\\t        \\\"approximation_notes\\\": [\\n   213\\t            \\\"Resolves surface-local spread on the simplified mesh and patch projection while abstracting away raw membrane biophysics and per-synapse state.\\\",\\n   214\\t            \\\"May change local spatial patterning relative to lower fidelities, but promotion must preserve root identity plus coupling sign, delay, and comparison-readout semantics.\\\",\\n   215\\t        ],\\n   216\\t        \\\"class_specific_behaviors\\\": [\\n   217\\t            \\\"Can express geodesic spread, patch-local heterogeneity, anisotropy, and descriptor-scaled branching when the wave model enables them.\\\",\\n   218\\t        ],\\n   219\\t    },\\n   220\\t}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T135208Z/FW-M11-001_Freeze_a_versioned_hybrid-morphology_contract_fidelity_taxonomy_and_approximation_design_note/stdout.jsonl:150:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_86\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"nl -ba docs/pipeline_notes.md | sed -n '300,380p'; nl -ba docs/hybrid_morphology_design.md | sed -n '1,220p'; nl -ba tests/test_hybrid_morphology_contract.py | sed -n '1,220p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"   300\\t  `surface_activation` (`activation_au`), `surface_velocity`\\n   301\\t  (`activation_au_per_ms`), and the optional `recovery_state` (`unitless`)\\n   302\\t- the propagation term is defined against the Milestone 6 mass-normalized\\n   303\\t  surface operator; damping is a separate linear sink on `surface_velocity`\\n   304\\t- synaptic injection semantics reuse Milestone 7 sign, delay, aggregation, and\\n   305\\t  landing-anchor rules and add the realized source to `surface_velocity`\\n   306\\t  through one named source mode `coupling_anchor_current`\\n   307\\t- recovery, nonlinearity, anisotropy, and branching now have explicit mode\\n   308\\t  identifiers in the contract even when the shipped default preset keeps them\\n   309\\t  disabled or in identity mode\\n   310\\t- the canonical v1 solver family identifier is\\n   311\\t  `semi_implicit_velocity_split`, and later stability checks are expected to\\n   312\\t  derive timestep guards from operator spectra rather than graph-degree rules\\n   313\\t- `resolve_surface_wave_model_metadata_path()` and\\n   314\\t  `build_surface_wave_model_reference()` are the discovery helpers later\\n   315\\t  planning, execution, and result code should use instead of hardcoded strings\\n   316\\t\\n   317\\t`docs/surface_wave_model_design.md` is the authoritative Milestone 10 decision\\n   318\\tnote; later tickets should cite it instead of re-litigating the chosen wave\\n   319\\tfamily, state-variable semantics, stability assumptions, or what counts as a\\n   320\\tnumerical artifact.\\n   321\\t\\n   322\\t### Hybrid morphology contract\\n   323\\t\\n   324\\tMilestone 11 now reserves one explicit mixed-fidelity vocabulary under the\\n   325\\tversioned contract `hybrid_morphology.v1`.\\n   326\\t\\n   327\\tContract notes:\\n   328\\t\\n   329\\t- class naming, class normalization, per-root metadata normalization, stable\\n   330\\t  class discovery, and the allowed cross-class route catalog now live in\\n   331\\t  `flywire_wave.hybrid_morphology_contract`\\n   332\\t- the canonical simulator-facing classes are `surface_neuron`,\\n   333\\t  `skeleton_neuron`, and `point_neuron`, normalized from the existing registry\\n   334\\t  roles `surface_simulated`, `skeleton_simulated`, and `point_simulated`\\n   335\\t- mixed fidelity stays inside the existing `surface_wave` planning path rather\\n   336\\t  than introducing a second top-level simulator mode; the planner writes the\\n   337\\t  normalized payload at `surface_wave_execution_plan.hybrid_morphology`\\n   338\\t- the normalized payload records:\\n   339\\t  - per class required and optional local assets\\n   340\\t  - realized state-space semantics\\n   341\\t  - local readout surface semantics\\n   342\\t  - incoming and outgoing coupling-anchor resolution\\n   343\\t  - serialization requirements for planning and result review\\n   344\\t  - approximation notes and intentional class-specific behavior\\n   345\\t- promotion order is `point_neuron -> skeleton_neuron -> surface_neuron`\\n   346\\t- promotion or demotion may refine intraneuron state resolution, but it may not\\n   347\\t  change selected root IDs, selected connectome edges, shared readout IDs,\\n   348\\t  shared timebase semantics, or Milestone 7 sign/delay/aggregation semantics\\n   349\\t- all source/target class pairs are explicit contract routes; the source class\\n   350\\t  supplies the presynaptic readout surface and outgoing anchor resolution, and\\n   351\\t  the target class supplies the landing surface and incoming anchor resolution\\n   352\\t- the same normalized payload is mirrored into surface-wave execution\\n   353\\t  provenance and the wave summary sidecar so later review tooling sees one\\n   354\\t  stable serialization surface\\n   355\\t\\n   356\\t`docs/hybrid_morphology_design.md` is the authoritative Milestone 11 decision\\n   357\\tnote; later tickets should cite it instead of re-litigating mixed-fidelity\\n   358\\tclass names, approximation limits, or promotion invariants.\\n   359\\t\\n   360\\t### Simulator result bundle contract\\n   361\\t\\n   362\\tMilestone 9 now reserves one explicit simulator-owned result surface under the\\n   363\\tversioned contract `simulator_result_bundle.v1`.\\n   364\\t\\n   365\\tThe library-owned default layout is:\\n   366\\t\\n   367\\t- `data/processed/simulator_results/bundles/<experiment_id>/<arm_id>/<run_spec_hash>/simulator_result_bundle.json`:\\n   368\\t  authoritative per-arm run metadata and artifact inventory\\n   369\\t- `data/processed/simulator_results/bundles/<experiment_id>/<arm_id>/<run_spec_hash>/state_summary.json`:\\n   370\\t  comparison-ready long-table state summaries\\n   371\\t- `data/processed/simulator_results/bundles/<experiment_id>/<arm_id>/<run_spec_hash>/readout_traces.npz`:\\n   372\\t  shared readout traces on the canonical simulator timebase\\n   373\\t- `data/processed/simulator_results/bundles/<experiment_id>/<arm_id>/<run_spec_hash>/metrics.csv`:\\n   374\\t  comparison-ready metric rows keyed by stable readout IDs\\n   375\\t- `data/processed/simulator_results/bundles/<experiment_id>/<arm_id>/<run_spec_hash>/extensions/<file_name>`:\\n   376\\t  deterministic execution logs, provenance, UI comparison payloads, and any\\n   377\\t  later model-specific diagnostics\\n   378\\t\\n   379\\tContract notes:\\n   380\\t\\n     1\\t# Hybrid Morphology Design\\n     2\\t\\n     3\\t## Purpose\\n     4\\t\\n     5\\tMilestone 11 needs one contract-owned vocabulary for mixed morphology fidelity\\n     6\\tbefore planner code, runtime glue, and result serialization encode different\\n     7\\tmeanings for the same run. The canonical contract is `hybrid_morphology.v1`,\\n     8\\timplemented in `flywire_wave.hybrid_morphology_contract`.\\n     9\\t\\n    10\\tThis note reuses earlier locked decisions instead of reopening them:\\n    11\\t\\n    12\\t- Milestone 7 already fixes coupling sign, delay, aggregation, and anchor\\n    13\\t  fallback semantics.\\n    14\\t- Milestone 9 already fixes the shared result-bundle timebase and readout\\n    15\\t  comparison surface.\\n    16\\t- Milestone 10 already fixes the `surface_wave` top-level mode plus the default\\n    17\\t  surface-wave family and state vocabulary.\\n    18\\t\\n    19\\tMilestone 11 therefore does not add a new top-level simulator mode. Mixed\\n    20\\tfidelity stays inside `surface_wave` through per-root morphology-class metadata.\\n    21\\t\\n    22\\t## Contract Summary\\n    23\\t\\n    24\\t`hybrid_morphology.v1` freezes three simulator-facing morphology classes:\\n    25\\t\\n    26\\t- `surface_neuron`\\n    27\\t- `skeleton_neuron`\\n    28\\t- `point_neuron`\\n    29\\t\\n    30\\tThe registry role aliases map directly:\\n    31\\t\\n    32\\t- `surface_simulated` -> `surface_neuron`\\n    33\\t- `skeleton_simulated` -> `skeleton_neuron`\\n    34\\t- `point_simulated` -> `point_neuron`\\n    35\\t\\n    36\\tThe planner-owned metadata lives at\\n    37\\t`surface_wave_execution_plan.hybrid_morphology`. Execution provenance and the\\n    38\\twave summary mirror the same normalized payload so review code sees one stable\\n    39\\tfield path.\\n    40\\t\\n    41\\t## Fidelity Classes\\n    42\\t\\n    43\\t### `point_neuron`\\n    44\\t\\n    45\\t- required local assets:\\n    46\\t  `root_local_synapse_registry`, `incoming_anchor_map`, `outgoing_anchor_map`,\\n    47\\t  `root_coupling_index`, `selected_edge_coupling_bundles`\\n    48\\t- optional local assets:\\n    49\\t  `raw_swc_skeleton`, `processed_surface_mesh`, `geometry_descriptors`\\n    50\\t- realized state space:\\n    51\\t  one root-local lumped state with optional auxiliary terms and no intraneuron\\n    52\\t  spatial resolution\\n    53\\t- readout surface:\\n    54\\t  `root_state_scalar`\\n    55\\t- coupling anchor resolution:\\n    56\\t  incoming and outgoing `lumped_root_state`\\n    57\\t- allowed approximation:\\n    58\\t  remove intraneuron propagation while preserving root identity, coupling sign,\\n    59\\t  coupling delay, and total signed weight semantics\\n    60\\t- intentional class-specific behavior:\\n    61\\t  cannot express branch-local or surface-local spread\\n    62\\t\\n    63\\t### `skeleton_neuron`\\n    64\\t\\n    65\\t- required local assets:\\n    66\\t  `raw_swc_skeleton`, `root_local_synapse_registry`, `incoming_anchor_map`,\\n    67\\t  `outgoing_anchor_map`, `root_coupling_index`,\\n    68\\t  `selected_edge_coupling_bundles`\\n    69\\t- optional local assets:\\n    70\\t  `processed_surface_mesh`, `surface_transfer_operators`,\\n    71\\t  `geometry_descriptors`\\n    72\\t- realized state space:\\n    73\\t  distributed activation over skeleton nodes or segments\\n    74\\t- readout surface:\\n    75\\t  `skeleton_anchor_cloud`\\n    76\\t- coupling anchor resolution:\\n    77\\t  incoming and outgoing `skeleton_node`\\n    78\\t- allowed approximation:\\n    79\\t  preserve branch and path structure while omitting explicit surface-sheet\\n    80\\t  geometry and patch-local tangential spread\\n    81\\t- intentional class-specific behavior:\\n    82\\t  may express branch-local timing or attenuation that a point neuron cannot,\\n    83\\t  but not surface-sheet effects reserved for `surface_neuron`\\n    84\\t\\n    85\\t### `surface_neuron`\\n    86\\t\\n    87\\t- required local assets:\\n    88\\t  `processed_surface_mesh`, `fine_surface_operator`, `coarse_patch_operator`,\\n    89\\t  `surface_transfer_operators`, `surface_operator_metadata`,\\n    90\\t  `root_local_synapse_registry`, `incoming_anchor_map`, `outgoing_anchor_map`,\\n    91\\t  `root_coupling_index`, `selected_edge_coupling_bundles`\\n    92\\t- optional local assets:\\n    93\\t  `raw_mesh`, `raw_swc_skeleton`, `geometry_descriptors`, `geometry_qa`\\n    94\\t- realized state space:\\n    95\\t  distributed surface field on the simplified mesh with patch projection\\n    96\\t- readout surface:\\n    97\\t  `coarse_patch_cloud`\\n    98\\t- coupling anchor resolution:\\n    99\\t  incoming and outgoing `coarse_patch`\\n   100\\t- allowed approximation:\\n   101\\t  retain surface-local spread while abstracting away raw membrane biophysics and\\n   102\\t  per-synapse state\\n   103\\t- intentional class-specific behavior:\\n   104\\t  may express geodesic spread, patch-local heterogeneity, anisotropy, and\\n   105\\t  descriptor-scaled branching when the wave model enables them\\n   106\\t\\n   107\\t## Cross-Class Coupling Routes\\n   108\\t\\n   109\\tAll nine source/target class pairs are contract-valid:\\n   110\\t\\n   111\\t- point -> point\\n   112\\t- point -> skeleton\\n   113\\t- point -> surface\\n   114\\t- skeleton -> point\\n   115\\t- skeleton -> skeleton\\n   116\\t- skeleton -> surface\\n   117\\t- surface -> point\\n   118\\t- surface -> skeleton\\n   119\\t- surface -> surface\\n   120\\t\\n   121\\tFor every route, the source class supplies the presynaptic readout surface and\\n   122\\toutgoing anchor resolution, while the target class supplies the landing surface\\n   123\\tand incoming anchor resolution. The route may change spatial support, but it\\n   124\\tmay not change Milestone 7 sign, delay, or aggregation semantics.\\n   125\\t\\n   126\\t## Promotion And Demotion Invariants\\n   127\\t\\n   128\\tPromoting `point_neuron -> skeleton_neuron -> surface_neuron`, or demoting in\\n   129\\tthe opposite direction, must preserve these meanings unless the contract version\\n   130\\tchanges:\\n   131\\t\\n   132\\t- selected root IDs and manifest-arm identity stay fixed\\n   133\\t- the selected connectome edge set stays fixed\\n   134\\t- shared readout IDs, units, and timebase stay fixed\\n   135\\t- coupling sign, delay, and aggregation semantics stay fixed\\n   136\\t- root-local input identity and comparison-readout meaning stay fixed\\n   137\\t- class-specific diagnostics may expand under `extensions/`, but shared result\\n   138\\t  payloads do not change shape or semantics\\n   139\\t\\n   140\\tPromotion is therefore allowed to refine intraneuron state resolution and local\\n   141\\tspatial patterning. It is not allowed to introduce a new decoder, new edges,\\n   142\\tnew per-synapse sign rules, or a new top-level model mode.\\n   143\\t\\n   144\\t## Serialization Rules\\n   145\\t\\n   146\\tEvery per-root class record must remain deterministic and include at least:\\n   147\\t\\n   148\\t- `root_id`\\n   149\\t- `morphology_class`\\n   150\\t- `source_project_role`\\n   151\\t- `promotion_rank`\\n   152\\t\\n   153\\tThe normalized contract payload is serialized in three places:\\n   154\\t\\n   155\\t- `surface_wave_execution_plan.hybrid_morphology`\\n   156\\t- `execution_provenance.json -> model_execution.hybrid_morphology`\\n   157\\t- `surface_wave_summary.json -> hybrid_morphology`\\n   158\\t\\n   159\\tShared comparison traces still live in `simulator_result_bundle.v1`. Class-\\n   160\\tspecific state or diagnostics may live under `extensions/`, but they may not\\n   161\\tmutate the shared readout catalog, shared trace layout, or shared metric table.\\n   162\\t\\n   163\\t## Scope Boundary\\n   164\\t\\n   165\\tThis note freezes the vocabulary for mixed morphology classes, approximation\\n   166\\tlimits, and promotion invariants. Later Milestone 11 tickets may implement more\\n   167\\tof the runtime, but they should cite this note instead of inventing new class\\n   168\\tnames or changing what `point_neuron`, `skeleton_neuron`, or `surface_neuron`\\n   169\\tmean inside one simulator run.\\n     1\\tfrom __future__ import annotations\\n     2\\t\\n     3\\timport json\\n     4\\timport sys\\n     5\\timport unittest\\n     6\\tfrom pathlib import Path\\n     7\\t\\n     8\\tROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\\n     9\\tSRC = ROOT / \\\"src\\\"\\n    10\\tsys.path.insert(0, str(SRC))\\n    11\\t\\n    12\\tfrom flywire_wave.hybrid_morphology_contract import (\\n    13\\t    HYBRID_MORPHOLOGY_CONTRACT_VERSION,\\n    14\\t    POINT_NEURON_CLASS,\\n    15\\t    SKELETON_NEURON_CLASS,\\n    16\\t    SURFACE_NEURON_CLASS,\\n    17\\t    build_hybrid_morphology_plan_metadata,\\n    18\\t    discover_hybrid_morphology_classes,\\n    19\\t    normalize_hybrid_morphology_root_metadata,\\n    20\\t    parse_hybrid_morphology_plan_metadata,\\n    21\\t)\\n    22\\t\\n    23\\t\\n    24\\tclass HybridMorphologyContractTest(unittest.TestCase):\\n    25\\t    def test_fixture_hybrid_metadata_normalizes_deterministically_and_discovers_classes(self) -> None:\\n    26\\t        fixture_a = [\\n    27\\t            {\\n    28\\t                \\\"root_id\\\": 303,\\n    29\\t                \\\"project_role\\\": \\\"point_simulated\\\",\\n    30\\t                \\\"cell_type\\\": \\\"Mi1\\\",\\n    31\\t            },\\n    32\\t            {\\n    33\\t                \\\"root_id\\\": 101,\\n    34\\t                \\\"project_role\\\": \\\"surface_simulated\\\",\\n    35\\t                \\\"cell_type\\\": \\\"T4a\\\",\\n    36\\t            },\\n    37\\t            {\\n    38\\t                \\\"root_id\\\": 202,\\n    39\\t                \\\"morphology_class\\\": \\\"Skeleton Neuron\\\",\\n    40\\t                \\\"cell_type\\\": \\\"TmY5a\\\",\\n    41\\t            },\\n    42\\t        ]\\n    43\\t        fixture_b = [\\n    44\\t            {\\n    45\\t                \\\"root_id\\\": 202,\\n    46\\t                \\\"project_role\\\": \\\"skeleton_simulated\\\",\\n    47\\t                \\\"morphology_class\\\": \\\"skeleton_neuron\\\",\\n    48\\t                \\\"cell_type\\\": \\\"TmY5a\\\",\\n    49\\t            },\\n    50\\t            {\\n    51\\t                \\\"root_id\\\": 101,\\n    52\\t                \\\"morphology_class\\\": \\\"surface-neuron\\\",\\n    53\\t                \\\"cell_type\\\": \\\"T4a\\\",\\n    54\\t            },\\n    55\\t            {\\n    56\\t                \\\"root_id\\\": 303,\\n    57\\t                \\\"morphology_class\\\": \\\"Point Neuron\\\",\\n    58\\t                \\\"project_role\\\": \\\"point_simulated\\\",\\n    59\\t                \\\"cell_type\\\": \\\"Mi1\\\",\\n    60\\t            },\\n    61\\t        ]\\n    62\\t\\n    63\\t        metadata_a = build_hybrid_morphology_plan_metadata(root_records=fixture_a)\\n    64\\t        metadata_b = build_hybrid_morphology_plan_metadata(root_records=fixture_b)\\n    65\\t        reparsed = parse_hybrid_morphology_plan_metadata(metadata_a)\\n    66\\t\\n    67\\t        self.assertEqual(metadata_a, metadata_b)\\n    68\\t        self.assertEqual(reparsed, metadata_a)\\n    69\\t        self.assertEqual(\\n    70\\t            metadata_a[\\\"contract_version\\\"],\\n    71\\t            HYBRID_MORPHOLOGY_CONTRACT_VERSION,\\n    72\\t        )\\n    73\\t        self.assertEqual(\\n    74\\t            metadata_a[\\\"planner_integration\\\"][\\\"field_name\\\"],\\n    75\\t            \\\"surface_wave_execution_plan.hybrid_morphology\\\",\\n    76\\t        )\\n    77\\t        self.assertEqual(\\n    78\\t            metadata_a[\\\"discovered_morphology_classes\\\"],\\n    79\\t            [\\n    80\\t                POINT_NEURON_CLASS,\\n    81\\t                SKELETON_NEURON_CLASS,\\n    82\\t                SURFACE_NEURON_CLASS,\\n    83\\t            ],\\n    84\\t        )\\n    85\\t        self.assertEqual(\\n    86\\t            discover_hybrid_morphology_classes(\\n    87\\t                [\\n    88\\t                    {\\\"project_role\\\": \\\"surface_simulated\\\"},\\n    89\\t                    {\\\"morphology_class\\\": \\\"point_neuron\\\"},\\n    90\\t                    {\\\"project_role\\\": \\\"skeleton_simulated\\\"},\\n    91\\t                    {\\\"morphology_class\\\": \\\"surface_neuron\\\"},\\n    92\\t                ]\\n    93\\t            ),\\n    94\\t            [\\n    95\\t                POINT_NEURON_CLASS,\\n    96\\t                SKELETON_NEURON_CLASS,\\n    97\\t                SURFACE_NEURON_CLASS,\\n    98\\t            ],\\n    99\\t        )\\n   100\\t\\n   101\\t        normalized_root = normalize_hybrid_morphology_root_metadata(\\n   102\\t            {\\n   103\\t                \\\"root_id\\\": 202,\\n   104\\t                \\\"project_role\\\": \\\"skeleton_simulated\\\",\\n   105\\t                \\\"cell_type\\\": \\\"TmY5a\\\",\\n   106\\t            }\\n   107\\t        )\\n   108\\t        self.assertEqual(normalized_root[\\\"morphology_class\\\"], SKELETON_NEURON_CLASS)\\n   109\\t        self.assertEqual(\\n   110\\t            normalized_root[\\\"coupling_anchor_resolution\\\"][\\\"incoming_resolution\\\"],\\n   111\\t            \\\"skeleton_node\\\",\\n   112\\t        )\\n   113\\t        self.assertEqual(\\n   114\\t            normalized_root[\\\"readout_surface\\\"][\\\"local_readout_surface\\\"],\\n   115\\t            \\\"skeleton_anchor_cloud\\\",\\n   116\\t        )\\n   117\\t\\n   118\\t        per_root = {\\n   119\\t            int(item[\\\"root_id\\\"]): item\\n   120\\t            for item in metadata_a[\\\"per_root_class_metadata\\\"]\\n   121\\t        }\\n   122\\t        self.assertEqual(per_root[101][\\\"morphology_class\\\"], SURFACE_NEURON_CLASS)\\n   123\\t        self.assertEqual(per_root[202][\\\"morphology_class\\\"], SKELETON_NEURON_CLASS)\\n   124\\t        self.assertEqual(per_root[303][\\\"morphology_class\\\"], POINT_NEURON_CLASS)\\n   125\\t        self.assertEqual(\\n   126\\t            per_root[101][\\\"realized_state_space\\\"][\\\"state_space_kind\\\"],\\n   127\\t            \\\"distributed_surface_field\\\",\\n   128\\t        )\\n   129\\t        self.assertEqual(\\n   130\\t            per_root[303][\\\"readout_surface\\\"][\\\"local_readout_surface\\\"],\\n   131\\t            \\\"root_state_scalar\\\",\\n   132\\t        )\\n   133\\t        self.assertEqual(\\n   134\\t            per_root[303][\\\"serialization_requirements\\\"][\\\"planner_record_fields\\\"],\\n   135\\t            [\\\"root_id\\\", \\\"morphology_class\\\", \\\"source_project_role\\\", \\\"promotion_rank\\\"],\\n   136\\t        )\\n   137\\t\\n   138\\t        route_ids = {\\n   139\\t            item[\\\"route_id\\\"]\\n   140\\t            for item in metadata_a[\\\"allowed_cross_class_coupling_routes\\\"]\\n   141\\t        }\\n   142\\t        self.assertIn(\\\"surface_neuron_to_point_neuron\\\", route_ids)\\n   143\\t        self.assertIn(\\\"point_neuron_to_surface_neuron\\\", route_ids)\\n   144\\t\\n   145\\t        serialized_a = json.dumps(metadata_a, indent=2, sort_keys=True)\\n   146\\t        serialized_b = json.dumps(metadata_b, indent=2, sort_keys=True)\\n   147\\t        self.assertEqual(serialized_a, serialized_b)\\n   148\\t\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T135208Z/FW-M11-001_Freeze_a_versioned_hybrid-morphology_contract_fidelity_taxonomy_and_approximation_design_note/stdout.jsonl:151:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_87\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Implemented FW-M11-001 end to end.\\n\\nThe main change is a new library contract module at [hybrid_morphology_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_contract.py#L15) that freezes `hybrid_morphology.v1` with canonical normalized classes `surface_neuron`, `skeleton_neuron`, and `point_neuron`, plus per-class required/optional assets, state-space semantics, readout surface semantics, coupling anchor resolution, serialization requirements, approximation notes, cross-class coupling routes, and promotion invariants. The existing `surface_wave` planning path now carries this at [simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py#L1565), and execution now normalizes/mirrors it into wave provenance and summary payloads in [surface_wave_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/surface_wave_execution.py) and [simulator_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/simulator_execution.py#L739).\\n\\nThe Milestone 11 vocabulary is documented in [hybrid_morphology_design.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/hybrid_morphology_design.md#L1), and [pipeline_notes.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/pipeline_notes.md#L322) now places mixed morphology alongside the other versioned contracts. Regression coverage was added in [test_hybrid_morphology_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_hybrid_morphology_contract.py#L24) and extended in [test_simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_simulation_planning.py) and [test_simulator_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_simulator_execution.py).\\n\\nVerified:\\n- `.venv/bin/python -m unittest tests.test_hybrid_morphology_contract tests.test_simulation_planning tests.test_simulator_execution -v`\\n- `make test`\\n\\nBoth passed. I left unrelated untracked `agent_tickets/...` files untouched.\"}}\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T135208Z/FW-M11-001_Freeze_a_versioned_hybrid-morphology_contract_fidelity_taxonomy_and_approximation_design_note/prompt.md:1:Work ticket FW-M11-001: Freeze a versioned hybrid-morphology contract, fidelity taxonomy, and approximation design note.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T135208Z/FW-M11-001_Freeze_a_versioned_hybrid-morphology_contract_fidelity_taxonomy_and_approximation_design_note/prompt.md:10:The repo now has strong contracts for geometry bundles, coupling bundles, retinal input, baseline execution, and `surface_wave` execution, but there is still no first-class contract for mixed morphology fidelity inside one simulator run. Role labels such as `surface_simulated`, `skeleton_simulated`, and `point_simulated` already exist in registry and coupling code, yet they do not currently define one canonical simulator-facing meaning for required assets, state layout, coupling anchor resolution, readout semantics, approximation limits, or promotion and demotion rules. Without a versioned hybrid contract, Milestone 11 work will drift across planner code, runtime glue, and result serialization, and it will be too easy to implement a mixed run that is operationally convenient but scientifically ambiguous.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T135208Z/FW-M11-001_Freeze_a_versioned_hybrid-morphology_contract_fidelity_taxonomy_and_approximation_design_note/prompt.md:18:- A dedicated markdown design note explains what each fidelity class is allowed to approximate, which semantics must remain invariant across promotion and demotion, and which behaviors are intentionally class-specific.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T135208Z/FW-M11-001_Freeze_a_versioned_hybrid-morphology_contract_fidelity_taxonomy_and_approximation_design_note/last_message.md:1:Implemented FW-M11-001 end to end.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T135208Z/FW-M11-001_Freeze_a_versioned_hybrid-morphology_contract_fidelity_taxonomy_and_approximation_design_note/last_message.md:3:The main change is a new library contract module at [hybrid_morphology_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/hybrid_morphology_contract.py#L15) that freezes `hybrid_morphology.v1` with canonical normalized classes `surface_neuron`, `skeleton_neuron`, and `point_neuron`, plus per-class required/optional assets, state-space semantics, readout surface semantics, coupling anchor resolution, serialization requirements, approximation notes, cross-class coupling routes, and promotion invariants. The existing `surface_wave` planning path now carries this at [simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py#L1565), and execution now normalizes/mirrors it into wave provenance and summary payloads in [surface_wave_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/surface_wave_execution.py) and [simulator_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/simulator_execution.py#L739).\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T135208Z/FW-M11-002_Extend_manifest_planning_and_config_normalization_for_per-root_fidelity_assignment_in_mixed_runs/stdout.jsonl:8:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_2\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc 'rg --files'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"scripts/04_validate_manifest.py\\nscripts/11_milestone8a_readiness.py\\nscripts/10_stimulus_bundle.py\\nscripts/run_simulation.py\\nscripts/build_registry.py\\nscripts/08_coupling_inspection.py\\nscripts/01_select_subset.py\\nscripts/00_verify_access.py\\nscripts/05_preview_geometry.py\\nscripts/07_milestone6_readiness.py\\nscripts/17_visualize_simulator_results.py\\nscripts/run_agent_tickets.py\\nscripts/09_milestone7_readiness.py\\nscripts/setup_flywire_token.py\\nscripts/14_milestone9_readiness.py\\nscripts/15_surface_wave_inspection.py\\nscripts/03_build_wave_assets.py\\nscripts/02_fetch_meshes.py\\nscripts/16_milestone10_readiness.py\\nscripts/13_milestone8b_readiness.py\\nscripts/06_operator_qa.py\\nscripts/12_retinal_bundle.py\\nRUN_ME_FIRST.md\\nagent_tickets/milestone_8b_retinal_ommatidial_sampler_tickets.md\\nagent_tickets/milestone_10_surface_wave_engin